title: Why this is not a flying kangaroo
text:
What are these? Roo on the runway: Kangaroos can jump so fast that it’s hard to spot them before it’s too late. Picture: Carmelo Bazzano Source: News Corp Australia 
A PASSENGER plane en route to Melbourne has hit a stray kangaroo on the runway at a regional Victorian airport, causing the flight to be cancelled. 
The roo was hit by a propeller of the Regional Express plane at Mildura airport as it was taxiing in the pre-dawn dark. 
Passengers were switched to a 10.30am flight and the plane is out of service while damage to the propeller is assessed. A Regional Express plane was put out of service after a kangaroo hit a propeller. File picture of a Regional Express plane. Source: News Limited
